headlines.description: — Luka Doncic made a 36-foot 3-pointer to beat the shot clock and blunt a late Sacramento rally and finished with 23 points in the Dallas Mavericks’ 105-99 victory over the Kings on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic hits long 3, Mavericks holds off Kings 105-99

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — The Charlotte Hornets signed free agent Kelly Oubre Jr. this offseason to provide energy off the bench and allow starting forward Gordon Hayward to rest a little more so he can make it through an 82-game season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball, Oubre lead Hornets past Trail Blazers, 125-113

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell helped the Utah Jazz bounce back from their first loss of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell helps Jazz win 107-95 as Bucks lose 3rd straight

headlines.description: — James Harden had 18 points, 10 rebounds, and 12 assists to power the Brooklyn Nets to a 117-91 rout of the Detroit Pistons on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden ties Bird with 59 triple-doubles as Nets rout Detroit

events.name: Houston Rockets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Carmelo Anthony scored 23 points in a reserve role and Russell Westbrook added 20 points in the Los Angeles Lakers’ 95-85 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carmelo Anthony scores 23, leads Lakers past Rockets 95-85
